Join us for a day of paddling on beautiful and Pristine Ossipee Lake. We'll launch from the Marina in the narrows between The main lake and Broad Bay from Lakefront Landing Marina and Campground Located at 85 Pequawket Trail Center Ossipee, NH

Ossipee Lake in Eastern New Hampshire. It's one of the largest lakes located entirely in New Hampshire. The stateâ€™s seventh largest lake, 3,092-acre Ossipee Lake and its extensive network of rivers and bays, is an excellent place for boating, and fishing.

NOTE: There is a $10 parking fee at the Lakefront Marina. Carpooling is a good idea if you want to save money on parking and share fuel costs.
